---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Notice — The Space Between"
  description="Privacy notice for between.sonicboom.org.uk: what data we collect, how we use it, and your rights. Run by Sonic Boom Music CIC."
>
  <main id="main">

    <!-- ── Page hero ────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <div class="page-hero">
      <div class="container page-hero__inner">
        <a href="/" class="page-hero__back">
          <span aria-hidden="true">←</span> Back to the site
        </a>
        <h1 class="page-hero__title">Privacy notice</h1>
        <p class="page-hero__sub">
          What we collect, why, and what you can do about it. Plain English.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ── Content ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <div class="page-content">
      <div class="container page-content__inner">

        <div class="prose">

          <h2>Who we are</h2>
          <p>
            This site is run by <strong>Sonic Boom Music CIC</strong>, a community interest
            company registered in England and Wales. Our address and registration details
            are available at <a href="https://www.sonicboom.org.uk/?utm_source=between&utm_medium=privacy&utm_campaign=sonicboom" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">sonicboom.org.uk <span class="sr-only">(opens in new tab)</span></a>.
          </p>
          <p>
            We are the data controller for personal data collected through this website.
            Contact us at <a href="mailto:hello@sonicboom.org.uk?subject=Privacy%20%E2%80%94%20The%20Space%20Between">hello@sonicboom.org.uk</a> with any questions.
          </p>

          <h2>What we collect and why</h2>

          <h3>Email address (and optional name)</h3>
          <p>
            If you sign up to The Space Between community, we collect your email address
            and, optionally, your name. We use these to send you information about upcoming
            events and community news. We use <strong>MailerLite</strong> to manage this
            — see their privacy policy at <a href="https://www.mailerlite.com/legal/privacy-policy" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">mailerlite.com/legal/privacy-policy <span class="sr-only">(opens in new tab)</span></a>.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>Lawful basis:</strong> consent. You can unsubscribe at any time using
            the link at the bottom of any email from us.
          </p>

          <h3>Postcode (optional)</h3>
          <p>
            We may ask for your postcode when you join the community or take part in the
            venue-demand poll. This is always optional and is never required. We use
            postcodes in aggregate form only — to understand how many responses come from
            each local area (e.g. how many from DE13, DE14). Individual postcodes are
            not stored against your personal record.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>Lawful basis:</strong> consent. Your postcode is handled in the same
            way as your email — you can ask us to delete it at any time.
          </p>

          <h3>Venue-demand poll responses</h3>
          <p>
            If you answer "Would you use a permanent grassroots music venue in Burton?",
            we record your choice (Yes / Maybe) and the date. We use this to build the
            demand evidence for our venue campaign. Your individual response is stored
            against a technical identifier (not your name or email) and combined with
            other responses to create an aggregate total.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>Lawful basis:</strong> legitimate interests (building evidence for a
            community venue campaign). You can ask us to delete your response at any time.
          </p>

          <h3>Analytics</h3>
          <p>
            This website uses <strong>Cloudflare Web Analytics</strong>, which does not use
            cookies, does not track individuals across sites, and does not store personal data.
            It measures aggregate page views and referrers only. There is no cookie banner on
            this site because none is required.
          </p>

          <h3>Technical data</h3>
          <p>
            Like all websites, this site is served via Cloudflare's network. Cloudflare
            may process your IP address as part of routing web traffic. See Cloudflare's
            privacy policy at <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">cloudflare.com/privacypolicy <span class="sr-only">(opens in new tab)</span></a>.
          </p>

          <h2>Tickets and event registration</h2>
          <p>
            Ticketed events use <strong>Ticket Tailor</strong> as our ticketing platform.
            When you buy a ticket or register for an event, you're sharing data with
            Ticket Tailor — see their privacy policy at <a href="https://www.tickettailor.com/privacy-policy" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">tickettailor.com/privacy-policy <span class="sr-only">(opens in new tab)</span></a>.
            We receive booking information (name, email, ticket type) to manage event
            attendance.
          </p>

          <h2>How long we keep your data</h2>
          <p>
            Email subscribers: until you unsubscribe, or ask us to delete your data.
          </p>
          <p>
            Event booking records: for up to two years after the event, for evaluation
            and reporting purposes (including Arts Council England grant conditions).
          </p>
          <p>
            Venue poll responses: for the duration of the venue campaign (currently
            expected to run until at least 2028), then reviewed.
          </p>

          <h2>Who we share your data with</h2>
          <p>
            We use the following processors:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>MailerLite</strong> — email delivery</li>
            <li><strong>Ticket Tailor</strong> — event ticketing and registration</li>
            <li><strong>Cloudflare</strong> — website hosting, analytics (cookieless)</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            We do not sell your data. We do not share it with third parties for marketing.
            We may share aggregate, anonymised statistics (e.g. "500 local residents have
            expressed interest in a music venue") with funders, the council, or press as
            part of the venue campaign.
          </p>

          <h2>Your rights</h2>
          <p>
            Under UK GDPR, you have the right to:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Access the data we hold about you</li>
            <li>Correct inaccurate data</li>
            <li>Ask us to delete your data</li>
            <li>Restrict how we use your data</li>
            <li>Receive your data in a portable format</li>
            <li>Object to processing based on legitimate interests</li>
            <li>Withdraw consent at any time (without affecting previous processing)</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            To exercise any of these rights, email
            <a href="mailto:hello@sonicboom.org.uk?subject=Data%20rights%20request%20%E2%80%94%20The%20Space%20Between">hello@sonicboom.org.uk</a>.
            We aim to respond within one month.
          </p>

          <h2>Complaints</h2>
          <p>
            If you're not satisfied with how we've handled your data, you have the right
            to complain to the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO) at
            <a href="https://ico.org.uk/make-a-complaint/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">ico.org.uk <span class="sr-only">(opens in new tab)</span></a>
            or by calling 0303 123 1113.
          </p>

          <h2>Changes to this notice</h2>
          <p>
            We'll update this page if our practices change. The date below shows when
            it was last reviewed.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>Last updated: June 2026</strong>
          </p>

        </div>

        <div class="page-back">
          <a href="/" class="btn btn-ghost-dark">
            <span aria-hidden="true">←</span> Back to the site
          </a>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* ── Page hero ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .page-hero {
    background: var(--ink);
    padding-block: clamp(var(--space-10), 8vw, var(--space-16));
    border-bottom: 3px solid var(--line);
  }

  .page-hero__inner {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-5);
  }

  .page-hero__back {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--body);
    text-decoration: none;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.4em;
    transition: color 150ms var(--ease-out);
    width: fit-content;
  }
  .page-hero__back:hover { color: var(--paper); }
  .page-hero__back:focus-visible {
    outline: 3px solid var(--ember);
    outline-offset: 4px;
    border-radius: 2px;
  }

  .page-hero__title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 7vw, 4.5rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    font-optical-sizing: auto;
    color: var(--paper);
    line-height: 1.0;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .page-hero__sub {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 2.5vw, 1.2rem);
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--body);
    max-width: 56ch;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ── Content ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .page-content {
    background: var(--paper);
    padding-block: clamp(var(--space-10), 8vw, var(--space-16));
  }

  .page-content__inner {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-12);
  }

  /* ── Prose ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .prose {
    max-width: 68ch;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
  }

  .prose h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 3vw, 1.75rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    font-optical-sizing: auto;
    color: var(--ink);
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin: var(--space-10) 0 var(--space-4);
  }
  .prose h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }

  .prose h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: var(--space-6) 0 var(--space-2);
  }

  .prose p {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: clamp(0.95rem, 2vw, 1.05rem);
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .prose ul {
    padding-left: var(--space-5);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }
  .prose li {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: clamp(0.95rem, 2vw, 1.05rem);
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .prose a {
    color: var(--red);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .prose a:hover { color: var(--ink); }
  .prose a:focus-visible {
    outline: 3px solid var(--ember);
    outline-offset: 3px;
    border-radius: 2px;
  }

  .prose strong { color: var(--ink); font-weight: 700; }

  /* ── Back link ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .page-back {
    padding-top: var(--space-6);
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(26, 18, 18, 0.1);
  }
</style>
